      <h1>New generation schemes are on hold</h1>
      <p>The Government’s sudden cut in the feed-in-tariff from around 11p to around 4.5p has shattered the business case for new, small generation schemes. The groups we’ve spoken to have either stopped developing generation projects, or are looking at very specific, limited sites that can work.</p>
      <p>But community energy groups aren’t going to give up that easily. Groups are looking around, searching for new types of projects they can experiment with.</p>
    </div>
