        <h1>We believe energy efficiency is a perfect match</h1>
        <p>We all know the energy hierarchy: saving energy wins over green generation, but energy efficiency has been fraught with policy failures and poor implementation.</p>
        <p>We believe community energy groups are in a perfect position to deliver energy efficiency improvements.</p>
        <p>Community energy groups can reach local people, raise money, and get people engaged in our future in way that a top-down, government scheme never can.</p>
        <p>Energy efficiency is tricky and we’re all still learning, so we need to start somewhere small.</p>

        <h2>LED light bulb retrofitting is a small, well-known starting point</h2>
        <p>Much like solar photovoltaics, LED light bulbs have undergone a technical revolution. Now their reduced price, excellent light quality and long life makes them an obvious choice for those who can afford them.</p>
        <p>But many can not, and have not switched to LED light bulbs. Our own research with people living in fuel poverty shows that ...</p>
        <p>The reality is that the people who would benefit the most from a saving on their bills are missing out.</p>
        <p>What if community energy groups funded the purchase of whole-house LED retrofitting, with support from Co-op to manage the fulfillment and support?</p>

        <h2>LED retrofitting is great value for money</h2>
        <p>We’ve been working with Sheffield Renewables to model how an LED retrofit project might work as a community energy project.</p>
