      <h1>Light House: a joint approach</h1>
      <p>Light House is a pilot project to make it simpler for community energy groups to deliver LED retrofitting.</p>
      <p>Community energy groups are excellent at raising community shares, engaging local people, and managing a community.</p>
      <p>However, community groups are likely to have difficulty administering large scale purchasing, delivery, management and customer service of a LED retrofitting scheme.</p>
      <p>Light House is designed to combine the strength and network of community groups with the scale and digital capabilities of the co-op.</p>

      <h2>Light House helps administer and run each project</h2>
      <p>Light House provides a digital platform to ease the delivery of LED retrofitting. The main responsibilities of the platform are:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Allowing a community to model a project with number of houses, cost of installation, percentage interest and so on</li>
        <li>Creating a draft share offer based on the model parameters</li>
        <li>Collecting information from households on what LED light types and fittings they require</li>
        <li>Bulk purchasing and delivering light bulbs to households</li>
        <li>Collecting weekly payment from households and distributing back to the community energy company</li>
        <li>Calculating interest payments to shareholders</li>
        <li>Calculating figures for accounts</li>
        <li>Managing warranty returns for any bulbs which break within warranty</li>
        <li>Creating period reports on energy and carbon savings achieved</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Community energy groups raise capital and manage their members</h2>
      <p>In much the same way community energy groups run today, groups have the following responsibilities:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Promoting &amp; administering the share offer (although share offers can be largely automatically generated)</li>
        <li>Recruiting households (either directly or through delivery partners such as housing associations)</li>
        <li>Managing relationships with delivery partners</li>
        <li>Welcoming &amp; involving new members (households and shareholders)</li>
        <li>Managing &amp; spending community benefit fund</li>
        <li>Normal running of the co-operative such as AGMs, events, accounts and outreach</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Households pay a weekly subscription</h2>
      <p>Households are responsible for a one-off assessment of what bulbs they need, assisted by the Light House service. They then commit to a £1 per week subscription for 3 years.</p>
